title: Pierre-Auguste Renoir Chrysanthemums Matted Note Card
description:
Print developed from Pierre-Auguste Renoir’s Chrysanthemums, 1881/82, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Pierre-August Renoir was a leading painter in the development of the Impressionist style. “He loves everything that is joyous, brilliant, and consoling in life,” an anonymous interviewer once wrote about Pierre-Auguste Renoir.

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image Dimensions: 4.25 x 5 in.
  • Full Dimensions: 8 x 10 in.
  • Materials: Premium cardstock.
